steps for git install 
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo apt-get install git

set up for git
 
git config –global user.email “your_emailid”
git config –global user.name “your_username”

git init - intialize git for the folder

Remote set up to tell where git is located
git remote add origin  https://github.com/your_username/myproject.git 

git congfig -l (gives the info)

Steps to add files in git hub

step 1 : create repo in the git. Name any thing you want.
step 2 : clone your project in local directory using git clone <URL>
step 3 : add files using git add . or git add <file name >
step 4 : commit the changes as git commit -m "your message "
step 5 : push the changes on remote using git push origin <branch name e.g master>
